{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878780033,"sessionID":"ses_285615463ffeogQeXC6JhObQY5","part":{"id":"prt_d7a9ee99d001VAdQnPl2iWpm92","messageID":"msg_d7a9ec71a001JvK7xO75tQnjTS","sessionID":"ses_285615463ffeogQeXC6JhObQY5","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_26c0a6bd4d9f43c484e34da8","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Delta Specification — AR-036: Dify 插件集成\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec documents acceptance scenarios for the AgentCube Dify plugin integration (AR-036) within the `integrations` module. It extends the base specifications in `integrations/design.md`, `integrations/spec.md`, `python-sdk/design.md`, and `python-sdk/spec.md`.\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Dify Plugin Package Structure\n\nThe system SHALL provide a complete Dify plugin package with all required files for plugin discovery and execution.\n\n### Scenario: Plugin package contains required files\n\n- **GIVEN** the plugin package root directory\n- **WHEN** the directory is inspected for file presence\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `main.py`, `manifest.yaml`, `provider/agentcube.yaml`, `provider/agentcube.py`, `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`, `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`, `requirements.txt`, and optional documentation files (`GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, `.difyignore`)\n\n### Scenario: Plugin entry point executes framework runner\n\n- **GIVEN** `main.py` contains the entry point code\n- **WHEN** the plugin process starts\n- **THEN** `main.py` SHALL execute `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Plugin Manifest\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `manifest.yaml` with all required Dify plugin metadata.\n\n### Scenario: Manifest contains required fields\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid `manifest.yaml` file\n- **WHEN** the manifest is parsed\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain:\n  - `version`: `\"0.0.2\"`\n  - `type`: `\"plugin\"`\n  - `author`: `\"volcano-sh\"`\n  - `name`: `\"agentcube\"`\n  - `label`: mapping for `en_US`, `ja_JP`, `zh_Hans`, `pt_BR` to `\"Agentcube\"`\n  - `description`: multilingual strings for AgentCube description\n  - `icon`: `\"icon.png\"`\n  - `icon_dark`: `\"icon-dark.png\"`\n  - `resource`: subtree with `memory`, `permission` (including `tool`, `model`, `endpoint`, `app`, `storage` flags and sizes)\n  - `plugins.tools`: list containing `provider/agentcube.yaml`\n  - `meta`: object with `version`, `arch` (`amd64`, `arm64`), `runner` (`language: python`, `version: \"3.12\"`, `entrypoint: main`), and `minimum_dify_version: null`\n  - `created_at`, `privacy`, `repo`, `verified`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Tool Provider Descriptor\n\nThe system SHALL provide a YAML descriptor for the AgentCube tool provider.\n\n### Scenario: Provider descriptor structure\n\n- **GIVEN** `provider/agentcube.yaml` exists\n- **WHEN** the descriptor is parsed\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain:\n  - `identity`: with `author`, `name`, multilingual `label` and `description`, and `icon`\n  - Optional commented `oauth_schema` block\n  - `tools`: list containing `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`\n  - `extra.python.source`: `\"provider/agentcube.py\"`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Tool Descriptor\n\nThe system SHALL provide a YAML descriptor for the code interpreter tool with complete parameter schema.\n\n### Scenario: Tool parameter schema definition\n\n- **GIVEN** `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` exists\n- **WHEN** the tool schema is parsed\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `identity.name`: `\"agentcube-code-interpreter\"`\n  - `identity.author`: `\"agentcube\"`\n  - `identity.label` / `description`: human and LLM-oriented strings\n  - `parameters`: list including:\n    | name | type | required | form |\n    |------|------|----------|------|\n    | `router_url` | string | true | form |\n    | `workload_manager_url` | string | true | form |\n    | `language` | select | false | llm (options: python, javascript, typescript) |\n    | `code` | string | false | llm |\n    | `command` | string | false | llm |\n    | `session_id` | string | false | llm |\n    | `session_reuse` | boolean | false | llm |\n    | `code_interpreter_id` | string | false | llm |\n  - `extra.python.source`: `\"tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py\"`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Provider Implementation\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Python implementation of the tool provider class.\n\n### Scenario: Provider class structure\n\n- **GIVEN** `provider/agentcube.py` exists\n- **WHEN** the module is imported\n- **THEN** it SHALL define `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` extending `ToolProvider` with a `_validate_credentials(self, credentials: dict[str, Any]) -> None` method that raises `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` on validation failure\n\n### Scenario: Provider credential validation passes\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` instance with valid credentials\n- **WHEN** `_validate_credentials` executes without errors\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return without raising\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Tool Implementation\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Python implementation of the code interpreter tool.\n\n### Scenario: Tool class structure\n\n- **GIVEN** `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` exists\n- **WHEN** the module is imported\n- **THEN** it SHALL define `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` extending `Tool` with:\n  - `_invoke(self, tool_parameters: dict[str, Any]) -> Generator[ToolInvokeMessage]` that calls `execute(**tool_parameters)` and yields `create_json_message(result)`\n  - `execute` method accepting parameters: `router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, `language` (default \"python\"), `code_interpreter_id`, `session_id`, `code`, `command`, `session_reuse` (default False), and `**kwargs`\n\n### Scenario: Tool returns JSON message\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` with valid parameters\n- **WHEN** `_invoke` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL yield a JSON message via `create_json_message`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Plugin Dependencies\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `requirements.txt` with pinned dependency versions.\n\n### Scenario: Dependency file content\n\n- **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`\n- **WHEN** the file is read\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain:\n  ```\n  dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0\n  agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10\n  ```\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: PCAP Analyzer Application\n\nThe system SHALL provide a FastAPI application that orchestrates PCAP analysis using AgentCube code interpreters.\n\n### Scenario: Application startup with API key\n\n- **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` is started with valid `OPENAI_API_KEY` environment variable\n- **WHEN** the application completes startup hooks\n- **THEN** it SHALL initialize `ChatOpenAI`, `PLANNER`, and `REPORTER` agents and bind to `0.0.0.0:8000`\n\n### Scenario: Application startup without API key\n\n- **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` is started without a valid `OPENAI_API_KEY`\n- **WHEN** the application attempts startup\n- **THEN** it SHALL fail during startup rather than serve requests\n\n### Scenario: Analyze endpoint accepts file upload\n\n- **GIVEN** a running service with valid LLM configuration\n- **WHEN** a client calls `POST /analyze` with a PCAP file upload\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL return `AnalyzeResponse` with `script`, `results`, and `report` fields\n\n### Scenario: Analyze endpoint accepts path parameter\n\n- **GIVEN** a running service with valid LLM configuration\n- **WHEN** a client calls `POST /analyze` with `pcap_path` form field\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL return `AnalyzeResponse` with `script`, `results`, and `report` fields\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: PCAP Analyzer Configuration\n\nThe system SHALL read configuration from environment variables with appropriate defaults.\n\n### Scenario: Default configuration values\n\n- **GIVEN** the service starts with only `OPENAI_API_KEY` set\n- **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n- **THEN** it SHALL use:\n  - `OPENAI_API_BASE`: default `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1`\n  - `OPENAI_MODEL`: default `Qwen/QwQ-32B`\n  - `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`: default `my-interpreter`\n  - `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`: default `default`\n  - `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC`: default `5`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: PCAP Analyzer Sandbox Integration\n\nThe system SHALL integrate with AgentCube sandbox via `SandboxRunner`.\n\n### Scenario: SandboxRunner initialization\n\n- **GIVEN** `SandboxRunner` is constructed\n- **WHEN** initialized with name, namespace, and warmup_sec\n- **THEN** it SHALL be ready to execute commands via `run()`, upload files via `upload_file()` and `upload_bytes()`, and can be stopped via `stop()`\n\n### Scenario: File upload to sandbox\n\n- **GIVEN** a local PCAP file or bytes\n- **WHEN** the orchestration calls `upload_file` or `upload_bytes`\n- **THEN** the artifact SHALL be available in the sandbox workspace for analysis\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: PCAP Analyzer Container Image\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Dockerfile for building the analyzer container.\n\n### Scenario: Dockerfile base and entrypoint\n\n- **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile`\n- **WHEN** built and run without overrides\n- **THEN** it SHALL use base image `ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:python3.12-bookworm-slim`, set `PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"`, expose port `8000`, and run `uv run pcap_analyzer.py`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: PCAP Analyzer Kubernetes Deployment\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Kubernetes deployment manifest.\n\n### Scenario: Deployment manifest structure\n\n- **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml`\n- **WHEN** applied to a cluster\n- **THEN** it SHALL create a Deployment with:\n  - Container image `pcap-analyzer:latest` with `imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent`\n  - Port `8000` TCP\n  - Resource requests: `cpu: 200m`, `memory: 100Mi`\n  - Resource limits: `cpu: 1`, `memory: 1Gi`\n  - Environment: `OPENAI_API_KEY` from Secret `pcap-analyzer-secrets` key `openai-api-key`, plus `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC`\n  - Command: `[\"uv\"]` with args `[\"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: AgentCube SDK Integration\n\nThe system SHALL use the AgentCube Python SDK for code interpreter and agent runtime operations.\n\n### Scenario: SDK client usage in tool\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool.execute` is invoked\n- **WHEN** the method processes parameters\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `CodeInterpreterClient` from the `agentcube` package to perform remote operations\n\n### Scenario: SDK client usage in analyzer\n\n- **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` runs analysis\n- **WHEN** it needs to execute code in a sandbox\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `CodeInterpreterClient` from `agentcube.code_interpreter`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Exception Handling\n\nThe system SHALL properly handle SDK exceptions.\n\n### Scenario: Command execution failure\n\n- **GIVEN** remote command returns non-zero exit code\n- **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command` attributes","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775878780009,"end":1775878780028}}}}
