{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775878801684,"sessionID":"ses_285615463ffeogQeXC6JhObQY5","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa00911001ZME7PtbSHX7fcM","messageID":"msg_d7aa002ca001jMzqdJeJ0rHLiC","sessionID":"ses_285615463ffeogQeXC6JhObQY5","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878873533,"sessionID":"ses_285615463ffeogQeXC6JhObQY5","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa00fad001wf9pc5Rr4cZkSI","messageID":"msg_d7aa002ca001jMzqdJeJ0rHLiC","sessionID":"ses_285615463ffeogQeXC6JhObQY5","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_0f69ccc4731145dfa5a86eef","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-036: Dify 插件集成 - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Dify plugin integration in the AgentCube `integrations` module.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-036\n- **Module**: `integrations`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Reference Sources**: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/integrations/dify-plugin/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`\n\n---\n\n## Files to Add\n\n| Path | Description | Type |\n|------|-------------|------|\n| `integrations/dify-plugin/main.py` | Plugin entry point executing `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` | New |\n| `integrations/dify-plugin/manifest.yaml` | Root plugin manifest for Dify | New |\n| `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.yaml` | Tool provider identity + tool list + Python entry | New |\n| `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` implementation | New |\n| `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` | Tool parameter schema | New |\n| `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` implementation | New |\n| `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt` | `dify-plugin` and `agentcube-sdk` dependency pins | New |\n| `integrations/dify-plugin/GUIDE.md` | Plugin usage guide | New |\n| `integrations/dify-plugin/README.md` | Plugin documentation | New |\n| `integrations/dify-plugin/PRIVACY.md` | Plugin privacy policy | New |\n| `integrations/dify-plugin/.difyignore` | Dify ignore file | New |\n| `integrations/dify-plugin/icon.png` | Plugin icon (light) | New |\n| `integrations/dify-plugin/icon-dark.png` | Plugin icon (dark) | New |\n| `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` | FastAPI app with agents and sandbox runner | New |\n| `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt` | FastAPI and LangChain dependencies | New |\n| `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` | Container image definition | New |\n| `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml` | Kubernetes deployment manifest | New |\n| `example/pcap-analyzer/README.md` | Analyzer documentation | New |\n\n---\n\n## Files to Modify\n\n| Path | Description | Change Type |\n|------|-------------|-------------|\n| | | |\n\n---\n\n## Files to Delete\n\n| Path | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| | |\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### AR-036-001: Dify Plugin Package Structure\n\nThe system SHALL provide a complete Dify plugin package with all required files for plugin discovery and execution.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-001-A — Plugin package contains required files\n\n- **GIVEN** the plugin package root directory at `integrations/dify-plugin/`\n- **WHEN** the directory is inspected for file presence\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `main.py`, `manifest.yaml`, `provider/agentcube.yaml`, `provider/agentcube.py`, `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`, `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`, `requirements.txt`, and optional documentation files (`GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, `.difyignore`)\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-001-B — Plugin entry point executes framework runner\n\n- **GIVEN** `main.py` is defined as the plugin entry point\n- **WHEN** the plugin process starts via the manifest-declared entrypoint\n- **THEN** `main.py` SHALL execute `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` until the host stops it\n\n---\n\n### AR-036-002: Plugin Manifest Structure\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `manifest.yaml` with all required Dify plugin metadata.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-002-A — Manifest contains required fields\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid `manifest.yaml` file\n- **WHEN** the manifest is parsed by a Dify-compatible toolchain\n- **THEN** the manifest SHALL include:\n  - `version`: `\"0.0.2\"`\n  - `type`: `\"plugin\"`\n  - `author`: `\"volcano-sh\"`\n  - `name`: `\"agentcube\"`\n  - `label`: mapping for `en_US`, `ja_JP`, `zh_Hans`, `pt_BR` to `\"Agentcube\"`\n  - `description`: multilingual strings for AgentCube description\n  - `icon`: `\"icon.png\"`\n  - `icon_dark`: `\"icon-dark.png\"`\n  - `resource`: subtree with `memory`, `permission` (including `tool`, `model`, `endpoint`, `app`, `storage` flags and sizes)\n  - `plugins.tools`: list containing `provider/agentcube.yaml`\n  - `meta`: object with `version`, `arch` (`amd64`, `arm64`), `runner` (`language: python`, `version: \"3.12\"`, `entrypoint: main`), and `minimum_dify_version: null`\n  - `created_at`, `privacy`, `repo`, `verified`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-002-B — Tool provider wiring\n\n- **GIVEN** the manifest `plugins.tools` references `provider/agentcube.yaml`\n- **WHEN** the plugin is loaded by Dify\n- **THEN** Dify SHALL resolve `provider/agentcube.yaml` and associate it with the Python module declared under `extra.python.source`\n\n---\n\n### AR-036-003: Tool Provider Descriptor\n\nThe system SHALL provide a YAML descriptor for the AgentCube tool provider.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-003-A — Provider descriptor structure\n\n- **GIVEN** `provider/agentcube.yaml` exists\n- **WHEN** the descriptor is parsed by the integration runtime\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain:\n  - `identity`: with `author`, `name`, multilingual `label` and `description`, and `icon`\n  - Optional commented `oauth_schema` block\n  - `tools`: list containing `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`\n  - `extra.python.source`: `\"provider/agentcube.py\"`\n\n---\n\n### AR-036-004: Tool Parameter Schema\n\nThe system SHALL provide a YAML descriptor for the code interpreter tool with complete parameter schema.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-004-A — Tool parameter schema definition\n\n- **GIVEN** `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` exists\n- **WHEN** the tool schema is parsed\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `identity.name`: `\"agentcube-code-interpreter\"`\n  - `identity.author`: `\"agentcube\"`\n  - `identity.label` / `description`: human and LLM-oriented strings\n  - `parameters`: list including:\n\n| name | type | required | form | notes |\n|------|------|----------|------|-------|\n| `router_url` | string | true | form | |\n| `workload_manager_url` | string | true | form | |\n| `language` | select | false | llm | options: python, javascript, typescript |\n| `code` | string | false | llm | |\n| `command` | string | false | llm | |\n| `session_id` | string | false | llm | |\n| `session_reuse` | boolean | false | llm | |\n| `code_interpreter_id` | string | false | llm | |\n\n  - `extra.python.source`: `\"tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py\"`\n\n---\n\n### AR-036-005: Provider Implementation\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Python implementation of the tool provider class.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-005-A — Provider class structure\n\n- **GIVEN** `provider/agentcube.py` exists\n- **WHEN** the module is imported\n- **THEN** it SHALL define `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` extending `ToolProvider` with a `_validate_credentials(self, credentials: dict[str, Any]) -> None` method\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-005-B — Provider raises validation error\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` instance with invalid credentials\n- **WHEN** `_validate_credentials` encounters an error condition\n- **THEN** the provider SHALL raise `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` with a string message derived from the failure\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-005-C — Provider validation passes\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` instance with valid credentials\n- **WHEN** `_validate_credentials` executes without errors\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return without raising\n\n---\n\n### AR-036-006: Tool Implementation\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Python implementation of the code interpreter tool.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-006-A — Tool class structure\n\n- **GIVEN** `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` exists\n- **WHEN** the module is imported\n- **THEN** it SHALL define `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` extending `Tool` with:\n  - `_invoke(self, tool_parameters: dict[str, Any]) -> Generator[ToolInvokeMessage]` that calls `execute(**tool_parameters)` and yields `create_json_message(result)`\n  - `execute` method accepting parameters: `router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, `language` (default \"python\"), `code_interpreter_id`, `session_id`, `code`, `command`, `session_reuse` (default False), and `**kwargs`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-006-B — Tool returns JSON message\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` with valid parameters\n- **WHEN** `_invoke` is called by Dify\n- **THEN** the tool SHALL yield `create_json_message(result)` for the outcome\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-006-C — Tool delegates to SDK client\n\n- **GIVEN** valid `router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, and optional `language` defaulting to `python`\n- **WHEN** the tool receives `code` and/or `command` with optional `session_id`, `session_reuse`, and `code_interpreter_id`\n- **THEN** the tool SHALL use the AgentCube Python SDK `CodeInterpreterClient` to perform the corresponding remote operations\n\n---\n\n### AR-036-007: Plugin Dependencies\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `requirements.txt` with pinned dependency versions.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-007-A — Dependency file content\n\n- **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`\n- **WHEN** dependencies are installed in a clean environment\n- **THEN** installs SHALL satisfy `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` and `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n\n---\n\n### AR-036-008: PCAP Analyzer FastAPI Application\n\nThe system SHALL provide a FastAPI application that orchestrates PCAP analysis using AgentCube code interpreters.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-008-A — Application startup with API key\n\n- **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` is started with valid `OPENAI_API_KEY` environment variable\n- **WHEN** the application completes startup hooks\n- **THEN** it SHALL initialize `ChatOpenAI`, `PLANNER`, and `REPORTER` agents and bind to `0.0.0.0:8000`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-008-B — Application startup without API key\n\n- **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` is started without a valid `OPENAI_API_KEY`\n- **WHEN** the application attempts startup\n- **THEN** startup SHALL fail with an error rather than serve requests without credentials\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-008-C — Analyze endpoint accepts file upload\n\n- **GIVEN** a running service with valid LLM configuration\n- **WHEN** a client calls `POST /analyze` with a PCAP file upload (`pcap_file` as `UploadFile`)\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL return `AnalyzeResponse` with `script`, `results`, and `report` fields\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-008-D — Analyze endpoint accepts path parameter\n\n- **GIVEN** a running service with valid LLM configuration\n- **WHEN** a client calls `POST /analyze` with `pcap_path` form field (alternative to file upload)\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL return `AnalyzeResponse` with `script`, `results`, and `report` fields\n\n---\n\n### AR-036-009: PCAP Analyzer Configuration\n\nThe system SHALL read configuration from environment variables with appropriate defaults.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-009-A — Default configuration values\n\n- **GIVEN** the service starts with only `OPENAI_API_KEY` set\n- **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n- **THEN** it SHALL use:\n  - `OPENAI_API_BASE`: default `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1`\n  - `OPENAI_MODEL`: default `Qwen/QwQ-32B`\n  - `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`: default `my-interpreter`\n  - `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`: default `default`\n  - `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC`: default `5`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-009-B — Environment variable overrides\n\n- **GIVEN** environment variables `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` are set\n- **WHEN** the service starts\n- **THEN** it SHALL use the provided values instead of defaults\n\n---\n\n### AR-036-010: PCAP Analyzer Sandbox Integration\n\nThe system SHALL integrate with AgentCube sandbox via `SandboxRunner`.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-010-A — SandboxRunner initialization\n\n- **GIVEN** `SandboxRunner` is constructed with name, namespace, and warmup_sec\n- **WHEN** initialization completes\n- **THEN** it SHALL be ready to execute commands via `run()`, upload files via `upload_file()` and `upload_bytes()`, and can be stopped via `stop()`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-010-B — File upload to sandbox\n\n- **GIVEN** a local PCAP path or bytes to analyze\n- **WHEN** the orchestration needs the artifact inside the sandbox workspace\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `upload_file` or `upload_bytes` on `SandboxRunner` before executing analysis commands\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-010-C — Command execution in sandbox\n\n- **GIVEN** a `SandboxRunner` with an active session\n- **WHEN** `run(command)` is invoked\n- **THEN** the runner SHALL execute the command in the remote sandbox context and return structured execution results\n\n---\n\n### AR-036-011: PCAP Analyzer Container Image\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Dockerfile for building the analyzer container.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-011-A — Dockerfile base and entrypoint\n\n- **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` is built\n- **WHEN** the container runs without overriding the command\n- **THEN** it SHALL use base image `ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:python3.12-bookworm-slim`, set `PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"`, expose port `8000`, and run `uv run pcap_analyzer.py`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-011-B — SDK vendoring\n\n- **GIVEN** the Dockerfile build context includes `sdk-python/agentcube/`\n- **WHEN** the image is built\n- **THEN** it SHALL copy the agentcube SDK into the image at `./agentcube/`\n\n---\n\n### AR-036-012: PCAP Analyzer Kubernetes Deployment\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Kubernetes deployment manifest.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-012-A — Deployment manifest structure\n\n- **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml`\n- **WHEN** applied to a cluster\n- **THEN** it SHALL create a Deployment with:\n  - Container image `pcap-analyzer:latest` with `imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent`\n  - Port `8000` TCP\n  - Resource requests: `cpu: 200m`, `memory: 100Mi`\n  - Resource limits: `cpu: 1`, `memory: 1Gi`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-012-B — Environment variable wiring\n\n- **GIVEN** the deployment is applied\n- **WHEN** the pod starts\n- **THEN** it SHALL have environment variables:\n  - `OPENAI_API_KEY` from Secret `pcap-analyzer-secrets` key `openai-api-key`\n  - `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-012-C — Process launch in cluster\n\n- **GIVEN** the deployment's container specification\n- **WHEN** Kubernetes starts the container\n- **THEN** the command SHALL be `[\"uv\"]` with args `[\"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n\n---\n\n### AR-036-013: SDK Integration\n\nThe system SHALL use the AgentCube Python SDK for code interpreter and agent runtime operations.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-013-A — SDK import in tool\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` is executed\n- **WHEN** the tool needs to communicate with AgentCube\n- **THEN** it SHALL import and use `CodeInterpreterClient` from `agentcube`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-013-B — SDK import in analyzer\n\n- **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` runs analysis\n- **WHEN** it needs to execute code in a sandbox\n- **THEN** it SHALL import `CodeInterpreterClient` from `agentcube.code_interpreter`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-036-013-C — SDK exception handling\n\n- **GIVEN** remote command returns non-zero exit code in JSON\n- **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` (from `agentcube.exceptions`) with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command` attributes\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC001: Plugin package contains all required files (main.py, manifest.yaml, provider files, tool files, requirements.txt)\n- [ ] AC002: Plugin entry point executes `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()`\n- [ ] AC003: manifest.yaml contains all required Dify plugin metadata fields\n- [ ] AC004: Provider descriptor (`provider/agentcube.yaml`) contains identity, tools list, and Python source reference\n- [ ] AC005: Tool descriptor (`tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`) contains complete parameter schema\n- [ ] AC006: Provider implementation raises `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` on invalid credentials\n- [ ] AC007: Tool implementation delegates to `CodeInterpreterClient` and returns JSON messages\n- [ ] AC008: requirements.txt pins `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` and `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n- [ ] AC009: PCAP analyzer validates API key at startup and fails if missing\n- [ ] AC010: PCAP analyzer `/analyze` endpoint accepts file upload or path parameter\n- [ ] AC011: PCAP analyzer uses default configuration values when env vars are not set\n- [ ] AC012: SandboxRunner provides upload_file, upload_bytes, run, and stop methods\n- [ ] AC013: Dockerfile uses uv base image, exposes port 8000, runs pcap_analyzer.py\n- [ ] AC014: Kubernetes deployment wires secrets and environment variables correctly\n- [ ] AC015: SDK exceptions (CommandExecutionError) are properly handled\n\n---\n\n## Configuration Changes\n\n| Key | Old Value | New Value | Description |\n|-----|-----------|-----------|-------------|\n| | | | |\n\n---\n\n## Database Schema Changes\n\n| Table | Change | SQL |\n|-------|--------|-----|\n| | | |\n\n---\n\n## API Changes\n\n### New APIs\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| POST | `/analyze` | Analyze PCAP file with LLM orchestration |\n\n### Modified APIs\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| | | |\n\n### Deprecated APIs\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| | | |\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Notes\n\n### Key Components\n\n| Component | Path | Description |\n|------|------|-------------|\n| Plugin Entry | `integrations/dify-plugin/main.py` | Dify plugin process entry |\n| Plugin Manifest | `integrations/dify-plugin/manifest.yaml` | Root plugin metadata |\n| Provider | `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.py` | Tool provider implementation |\n| Tool | `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` | Code interpreter tool |\n| PCAP Analyzer | `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` | FastAPI application |\n| Sandbox Runner | `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` | AgentCube sandbox integration |\n| Deployment | `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml` | Kubernetes deployment |\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `OPENAI_API_KEY` | (required) | OpenAI-compatible API key |\n| `OPENAI_API_BASE` | `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1` | API endpoint |\n| `OPENAI_MODEL` | `Qwen/QwQ-32B` | Model name |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | (required) | AgentCube Workload Manager URL |\n| `ROUTER_URL` | (required) | AgentCube Router URL |\n| `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` | `my-interpreter` | Code interpreter name |\n| `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` | `default` | Kubernetes namespace |\n| `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` | `5` | Sandbox warmup duration |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Base design: `integrations/design.md`\n- Base spec: `integrations/spec.md`\n- SDK design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n- SDK spec: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n- Dify plugin source: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/integrations/dify-plugin/`\n- PCAP analyzer source: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-036/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-036/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-036/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775878873499,"end":1775878873530}}}}
